2pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">” </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">(p5)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Our area is one such area, whereby higher levels of environmental and social outcomes will not be realised if our ability to set local sustainability standards is removed. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">3.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Evidence of the high levels of sustainability achieved ain Brighton &amp; Hove through the work of the Local Planning authority is provided in the hyperlinked document on the Brighton &amp; Hove City Council website: </span><a href="http://www.brighton-hove.gov.uk/sites/brighton-hove.gov.uk/files/Delivering%20sustainable%20development%20B%26H%20Aug%2013.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Delivering good and advanced practice in sustainable development in Brighton &amp; Hove</span></a><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Brighton &amp; Hove</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">City</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold"> Council 2013)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">4.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">On a national level, the HSR proposals on sustainability </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">risk </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">a serious rollback of progress towards sustainable construction</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> and would </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">lock us into a lower build quality for the lifetime of </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">new homes to be built.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Higher local standards are needed to kick start the innovation and adoption process, enabling areas such as ours to stimulate innovation and early adoption, increasing uptake and reducing costs so other areas can follow. Under the proposals in the HSR, this first step of the innovation and adoption process would be lost. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">5.  The HSR Impact Assessment has failed to properly audit the impact of withdrawing the Code for Sustainable Homes (CSH) and withdrawing the ability of some local authorities to seek higher sustainability standards in their area where viable.  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">6.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">This assessment has not been undertaken in terms of the costs to the public or private sector. Neither has it assessed the sustainability or carbon impacts of the proposed options. In particular it has not assessed impacts from the reduced standards that will result from the proposed changes achieved in those areas that are currently achieving technical standards in advance of even the higher tier of technical standards proposed.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">3 October 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>